JRtfTree Library is a set of classes written entirely in Java that may be used to manage RTF documents in your own applications. 

JRtfTree is licensed under The GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPLv3).

JRtfTree will help you:

* Open and parse RTF files.
* Analyze the content of RTF files.
* Add, modify and remove document elements (i.e. text, control words, control symbols).
* Create new RTF documents.

You can find up-to-date information about JRtfTree Library at:

http://www.sgoliver.net/blog/?page_id=92